{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"Simple-Usage","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Simple Usage"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Extracting symbols from a string or contents of a file using "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"extract(from:visitor:)"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["import HatchParser","","let path = \"~\/Repositories\/monorepi\/libraries\/SUPI\/SUPI\/Classes\/NetworkUpdates\" as NSString","let directoryURL = URL(fileURLWithPath: path.expandingTildeInPath)","let fileURLs = FileManager.default.filesInDirectory(directoryURL)","let symbols = try fileURLs.flatMap { try extract(from: String(contentsOf: $0)) }","","dump(symbols)"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You can use swift standard library methods to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"filter"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"map"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"compactMap"},{"type":"text","text":" etc. "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"HatchParser"},{"type":"text","text":" provides an additional method on a collection of symbols or a "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/HatchParser\/documentation\/HatchParser\/Symbol"},{"type":"text","text":" called "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/HatchParser\/documentation\/HatchParser\/Symbol\/flattened()"},{"type":"text","text":" that returns a flat array of symbols derived from the symbol tree while preserving the subtree"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For example, to extract all the enum case elements from a specific enum, you can do:"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["symbols","    .filter { $0.name == \"ContentType\" }","    .first?","    .flattened()","    .compactMap { $0 as? EnumCaseElement }","    .map(\\.name)"]},{"anchor":"Advanced-Usage","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Advanced Usage"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Extending "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"HatchParser"}]},{"type":"orderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Sublass "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"SymbolVisitor"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Override the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"visitPost(_ node:)"},{"type":"text","text":" methods to create your own symbol."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Pass in your custom visitor to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"extract(from:visitor:)"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The following listing shows an example of adding generic where clause support:"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["class MySpecialVisitor: SymbolVisitor {","    override func visitPost(_ node: StructDeclSyntax) {","        if let genericWhereClause = node.genericWhereClause {","            endScopeAndAddSymbol { children in","                MySpecialStruct(","                    name: node.identifier.text,","                    children: children,","                    genericWhereClause: genericWhereClause.description","                )","            }","        } else {","            super.visitPost(node)","        }","    }","}","","struct MySpecialStruct: Symbol {","    let name: String","    let children: [Symbol]","    let genericWhereClause: String","}"]}]}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":2,"patch":0},"sections":[],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/hatchparser"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/HatchParser\/documentation\/HatchParser","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"HatchParser is an simple, extensible symbol parser based on "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"SwiftSyntax"}],"kind":"symbol","metadata":{"roleHeading":"Framework","externalID":"HatchParser","title":"HatchParser","symbolKind":"mod